Subject: Contributing to OSS - Navigating Community
Description: Hacking Open Source Software is the entire point of its existence.  Change what you don't like, fix what doesn't work for you, and enjoy.  But what about getting your patches accepted by the project? wrowe@apache.org and other participants invite you to this discussion on navigating communities, finding acceptance for your contributions, and becoming part of the bigger communities of Open Source Projects.  Speakers include:Willaim A. Rowe, Emily Gonyer - Track: Tech  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none
